Their menu is a bit underwhelming though, and their burgers tasted like Chili’s burgers so not bad but nothing special. It’s a nice place, and I like having seating spread out because of covid so it’s not super loud. I guess if you’re looking for a bite to eat and adult beverages you shouldn’t be too disappointed but it’s nothing special.
Food and beer were great, service was exceptional! I would definitely recommend this place to anyone.

Wing were soo good like I was very pleased

OMG ! Best Nachos I had this year. This restaurant was just around the corner and since the game was on I decided to enjoy the outdoor patio. Surprisingly the food is not too expensive,  I mean for Boston,  paid around $38 dollars for 3 people . Overall quality service was great,  food was good too and well presented but my Nachos were completely well made exactly how I want it. Love to be at Rock Bottom!
good food and good prices

Not bad, but not great. Just somewhere in the middle. First time in Boston, quick supper before heading in to hotel. I would have given a third star but my food was too salty and that's coming from a person that seasons their food. Overall, it's an okay option for American style food within the downtown/Chinatown area.
Not bad

This place is doubtless one of the coolest restaurants in the region. Anytime I come to this place I am highly satisfied. They hold their very high  standard service and the highest level of food  they give. You definitely will enjoy this this place. Very  recommended.

Wings were perfectly cooked and the Fireman's burger was great, albeit very messy. I ended up eating it with a knife and fork. Definitely a better choice than the hotel bar. Drink was done right too. Strong enough to know the booze was there but not over powering either.  As a tour bus driver from NY it's not often I get to stay in the city let alone have a chance to go out to eat. If ever I had the chance to be in Boston again I would stop here again.
Great service and food. Came here twice on this vacation!

Pleasant atmosphere. Satisfying menu. Wait staff was on point. I recommend it for your typical American fair. I had a kolsch beer and the fish and chips, and they were both quite good. Pleasant surprise: I tasted the first cole slaw I have ever enjoyed. It was not as heavy with mayonnaise as most, and it had (spoiler alert!) strips of apple that were hidden in with the slaw. They made for a nice sweetness and a healthy crunch.
Very welcoming and fun hostess...uninspired food, pricing average
Great spot. Excellent staff. Good food at a fair price. They cut their pizza weird.
Awesome atmosphere and great food.

I should have taken a video but really didn’t want to get anyone in trouble. All I will say is a question the “hygiene” and safe-serve training of the staff and management. We sat at the bar and a container of wilts, black celery was at the service station. Then one of the “floor managers” was serving drinks .. cut limes with “tongs” for use in garnish - right in the service station where staff place their serving trays .. gross . Too bad as the staff was friendly
Good food and great service

Average comfort food, some items were very good (ribs) some were lacking (fries). It’s 6pm. On a Tuesday. Music is so loud I can’t hear my server. And the server took 21 minutes from the time I sat down at my table until he came over. I put my order in. He brought the glass of wine, the soup, and the burger all at the same time. It all tastes mediocre. Disappointing experience.
Nice atmosphere and super amiable service. The meals were crisp and enchanting. Will clearly recommend this spot to friends. Fair rates and generous portions. Keep it up.

Ordered a double fireman burger however I wanted a single patty instead of a double. The menu didnt list it as a single patty burger. I ask the server she said no problem. When the bill arrives I got charged for the double I asked if it was a mistake. She said no that's what the price is. A single party burger here costs 10 and a double cost 15. I basically paid for a double party but only got one. RIP OFF. I hope this finds it way to a manager.

Busy night, they said wait would be 45mins, it was an hour and 15mins, hostess not very professional and rude to some customers, food was very salty, a couple beers on menu not available. Unfortunately not a good experience.

Visited on a Thursday before a show at the Wilbur. Did not expect to need a reservation, but luckily was tipped off and got one that afternoon. Had a very good dinner experience. Despite being stuck in traffic and a 15 minute late arrival they were nice enough to honor our reservation, they easily could have said "sorry" and I would have understood.  Little trouble ordering beer as three options were out, the waitress was clearly frustrated with the situation and lack of an updated menu, however we worked through it without a problem. Food came in a timely manner, I had the pulled pork sandwich which was very good, however nothing super special. Others had burgers and each raved about how good they were, and after trying a bite I must admit they make a great burger here, not sure what their trick is but I regretted not getting one.  We were on our way across the street just in time for the show. Great spot, just get a reservation.
Food is really good. But they have lost our families reservation two years now. We even have a confirmation to show them. At least they sat our group but they squished us into one booth.
Nachos were very good and huge! Burger was excellent, perfectly cooked , but fries  were extremely salty. Our waitress, Yamile, was  excellent. Just an average place, but had great service!

Been here before the nachos are good and huge say at least four people can share these, but I got some special burger, gouda cheese and french onions, horrible. And some special sauce or something. The service (if you can even call it that) is terrible!!! The hostesses were too busy playing on their phones to even notice we walked in & then our server never even showed up. We walked out after waiting around for 15 mins - I’d be surprised if they even noticed we left. Do not come here unless you’ve hit rock bottom!

Horrible sports awareness!! Literally turned off the world series game 1 at the bottom of 8th inning at 11:40pm; 20 minutes still remaining till close with a 5-4 game. Good place to eat and drink but not to watch sports! This was not a regular baseball game.. Literally game 1 of the world series! Had to cross the street to see the last inning because based on their explanation if you turn on the tvs the music and rest of the surround system will turn on too. If this happened during game 1 of the world series do not even think of watching a superbowl or nba finals at this place.

Sad to say but just all around terrible service. The bus boy was clearly a main contributor, as multiple servers had to bus their own tables, despite busy crowds; felt bad for them on a busy football Sunday.  The beers were good, the food was just okay. It took 10 mins to even be greeted by our server. 15 mins to get our second round of drinks (maybe if the busser was cleaning tables instead of standing around, this may have been different). Would have ordered a third or fourth round had we not had empties sitting for 15+ minutes before being asked for more.  Not sure if this is the norm or not but definitely won't be heading back, not even just for a pint.
Pretty good place to have a meal and watch a game. Lively atmosphere. Food is good and the beer is cold. Not extremely kid-friendly.
Pizza was great. Service was awful.

Service and food are really rock bottom. Wait for 10 minutes to get table ready, no menus, no water, no one comes to serve. Order lemon salmon, salmon is blackened, bitter to taste. Too bad cannot upload a picture of the salmon. Kids menu serve with Cajun fries.
Delicious steak salad. Even the tomato wedges had a nice smokey flavor

Stopped in for dinner and waa nit disappointed.  Tried both the Rocktober ale and their Irish Red ale.  Both were outstanding, their brewmaster knows their craft.  Had the jambalaya for dinner and it was excellent and fairly priced. I will definitely go back when I'm in Boston again.
Good: ambiance, drinks. Could be better: service.
Very poor customer service. Servers are so bad
they have a pretty good selection of on tap beers if youre in to that. if not, dont know what to tell ya
When first walked in, wasn't greeted, but once we got our waiter, he was very friendly and prompt at getting our drinks and food.

Absolutely terrible customer experience.  From the moment we walked into the establishment, our host would not agree to seat us, claiming it was not possible to seat a party of 6 outside for dinner on a warm Saturday evening, despite the 8 open tables. He turned us away at the door. We spoke with a manager that was able to begrudgingly push two tables together.  Our night didn’t get better. Our waitress left our table mid drink order for no apparent reason and returned only to forgot to take the order of someone in our party.  I’m surprised this restaurant is able to compete in downtown Boston’s restaurant scene. I can’t imagine people that value basic customer service return to this establishment.

Greasy goodness. The atmosphere is super loud but I think I was super hungry so I didn't really care. I do remember it was a super cold winter and the poor couple who sat next to the door had to eat in their jackets.

Wow..was so excited to go here as our local rock bottom closed recently. Sat down. Waited. Waited some more. Finally got up to leave and told the two guys at front that no on ever came to take our order. They just nodded. So disappointed.

Went to Boston and had dinner here. Food good however the service was as bad as it could get. As we went in we asked for a table and were allocatd a table that wasn't clean. When I asked to clean the table, the guy who walked us in gave me an attitude. During the meal, and before we were done, the waiteress brought us the check. We told her that we were not done yet and we were going for deserts so she took the bill back. At this stage we had not asked for the check yet. Of course, when the bill came we were not generous on our gratuity. I gave about $4.00 of gratuity only. However, when I received my bank statement tha tip charged to my credit card had been $14.00. In short, they took $10.00 more without my consentment. I was ROBBED. I contacted my credit card company, but I din't have the slip that shows the gratuity. Please remeber that in the U.S., they give you a printout of the bill and then you add the gratuity by hand. I only had the slip with the amount of the bill without the gratuity. LESSON: In this restaurant service is very poor and you are ROBBED. You don't need to be mugged in the streets. You will be mugged in the restaurant itself. Be careful in trusting them your credit card and don't expect a good service.

walked in late-night Saturday(seemingly popular but not overcrowded) with our 2 daughters (9 & 7 y/o ...don't worry not past their bedtime!)  cool sports-bar-y atmosphere, great service, really great food. Worse food ever!!!

Thought this looked like a neat place. My fiancé and I decided to come in for dinner on a Thursday evening. When we got inside, the host at the door had his back to us on the phone for about 5 minutes while we stood there. We got fed up with waiting so we asked a waitress who walked by if she could seat us. She said "no" and pointed at the host. We told her we had been standing there for 5 minutes and he's been on the phone the whole time. She gave us the most sarcastic, irritated smile I have ever seen and said "where do you wanna sit, then?" At this point we turned around and walked out. This is a great place for out of town guests. I know I'll be bringing mine.
The service was beyond expectations.  The food was amazing.  Super nice place,  great experience.

Stopped there with my boyfriend before seeing a show at the Wilbur. The Service was great! We sat at the bar and the lady and gentlemen who took care of us were super nice but the food in my opinion was a little over priced and not the greatest quality. I got the veggie burger which was okay but the veggies (Brussel sprouts and broccoli) were cold and had no flavor. You could tell they were frozen veggies not fresh, and in that case at least season them to taste decent. But again, the service was great !
This place is amazing! The carrot cake is expensive but well worth it! The sizes exceeded my expectations and the food left little taste buds dancing on my tongue 😩😄😄

I went for dinner the other night and sat at the bar expecting a quick bite and a beverage. Try the spicy chicken, it was hearty, tasty, and the chicken was tender.  It paired great with a Freedom Trail IPA.  I would definitely recommend Rock Bottom to friends.

Service was great!
Perfect for beer and snacks :)
Appetizers and decent tins. Nice servers. Solid place.

This is not a pizza place, I get it. But Jesus, not even passable. I would have been happier with a grocery store tombstone pizza. Tomatoes used we're the same ones used for burgers and literally no sign of any tomatoes sauce. Can't speak for anything else. My colleagues seemed to be mildly content with their burgers. But to screw up a pizza is like burning toast. Takes a special kind of lazy/stupid. Thanks for wasting calories.

Everything about this place was awesome. Great place to go before a show to kind of camp out. Host was so sweet and conversational. Even helped us with directions ! My server was great too. Food was pretty well prepared
Great wings , great beer, and great service
Banging!

Cheap options and an amicable atmosphere. Has plenty of tables for a sit-down meal and also a bar.

The service was efficient despite it being very busy. Friendly and prompt. Excellent menu with a wide range of food and drink at great prices. Loved the atmosphere. It was crowded but spacious and very comfortable. The salmon was delicious.

Great place. Good beer selection, great vibes, solid bar food and really good service.

Awesome Firehouse Burger.   Excellent service by Nick T.

Started off great but ended very oddly.  Our server Kota was very nice and friendly. Took our food and beverage orders. Everything was brought out to us, she checked on us a couple of times and we were all good. Then about a 1/2 hour goes by and she has not been back. We see her serving her other tables with no problems but we are just there. One person in our group whistles to get her attention, yes probably a little much but we were being ignored. She comes over, asks how she can help us, we let her know that we would just like the check and she responds by saying she will get our server. Ummm ma'am,  you are our server. About 5 minutes later the, what I am assuming is the manager comes over and asks if all is okay. We say yes, just waiting on the check. He brings the check and leaves. I notice there are 2 charges on the bill that don't belong to us. I let him know, he removes them. He then proceeds to try and rush us out of the restaurant. Needless to say between the server and the managers attitudes and treatment we didn't leave a tip. Which is sad because like I started off with we had a quite enjoyable start to the evening. I believe she may of just forgotten about us which is cool. Just own it and apologize.
Good service okay beer (limited selection) and great southwest egg rolls.

If the kitchen is going to prepare an unseasoned, fried variation, instead of the blackened fish taco described on the menu, the waitress should come out and make sure that is ok with the customer before serving it. My husband ordered a glass of sauvignon blanc, but the wine he received was really effervescent. When he told the server that it did not seem right, she just said ‘you don’t like it, I will take it off the check’. When we got the check, the wine she had to adjust from our check was a muscato; had she asked the bartender if the wine he served was a sauvignon blanc, she would have realized her error and could have corrected it. We have had great meals here before, so lunch today was disappointing.

I am so embarrassed I trusted a Rock Botttom hostess. Won't happen again.

drinks are great, atmosphere is great, and everyone should try the nachos!

Loved this place from the great drinks made at the bar to the food which was very good.And had the best server I've ever had.If you want great service ask for Gerardo,he was such a great server.Had to be at a show and he had us right on time.Will def be going back!

Stayed at a hotel down the street, came here everyday for dinner. Hospitable staff, unbelievably friendly, would suggest visiting if you're in town. Big shout out to the red headed bartender with the beard, guy was a class act !

We chose delivery because my wife was nursing our baby.  Bad experience.  They can’t follow directions and management sucks.  We won’t use them again.
Food was really good, beer was ok, nothing fantastic. Non alcoholic drinks were very good, as my wife had one of those. Atmosphere was good and so was the service.
Nice food, but very long service.
Wait,,, Wait,,, to be seated! For 1. but 2 pepper no salt! ASK ASK ASK for everything. for get it. How you stay in business is dumb luck. See the beer of the week? me nether☹

very nice environment. huge nachos (you can eat easily in two or three people). very tasty meat (Texas Steak is superb). impeccable service and very kind. Recommended!!!!

My wife and I have eaten here twice now in the last month and a half before a show in the city. We have eaten here before in the past too. The last two times that we ate here, we were not impressed with the service and I was not impressed with my food. When we ate here a month and a half ago, they messed up my wife’s order, but didn’t send it back because the waiter was no where to be found. Tonight, she did like her mac & cheese, but my brother-in-law and his girlfriend both ordered a SIDE Caesar salad. The waiter asked if they both wanted to add chicken. She said no and he said yes. They brought her a side Caesar and him a full Caesar with chicken. We were not able to correct his order as again our waiter was no where to be found. When the bill came, she was charged for a full Caesar at $9.99 and he was also charged for a full Caesar with chicken though he order a side. I informed the waiter of this and he fixed the price of her salad, but informed us that my brother-in-law’s salad only came in full because it had chicken. I told him that he ordered a side and that he had asked him if he wanted to add chicken to it. I also informed him that he should have made him aware that the side did not come with chicken and he would be getting a full salad and be changed for a full salad, as it was double to price. For these last times we ate at this restaurant, we were there for shows in the area. We didn’t have time to wait for our waiter to check back in and correct our above issues, nor should we have to wait for a waiter to check in. The waiters never made it a point to check in once dropping the food off at the table. Our waters never were refilled and plates weren’t cleared from the table. I understand that this is a busy area, especially when there are shows going on, but that doesn’t excuse poor service. Needless to say, moving forward, my wife and I will no longer be dining at this restaurant.
